== Troubleshooting ==

* I got an "End of file during parsing" error when I started Emacs.

** You might have missing or extra parentheses, quotation marks, or other characters. Open your init file and review the code carefully. You can use ##M-x check-parens## to find unmatched parentheses, brackets, or quotation marks.

* I put something in my ##~/.emacs.d/init.el##, but it didn't get loaded when I started Emacs.
** Emacs checks for the existence of one of these files, in order: ##~/.emacs##, ##~/.emacs.el##, ##~/.emacs.d/init.el##, ##~/.config/emacs/init.el##. It stops at the first file found and ignores the rest. Check if ##~/.emacs## exists. You can move the contents of that file to your ##~/.emacs.d/init.el## and delete ##~/.emacs## in order to use ##~/.emacs.d/init.el## instead.

* Something causes an error when I start Emacs.

** After starting Emacs, type ##C-h e## or use ##M-x view-echo-area-messages## to see any messages or errors from when it loaded. See DebugFileLoading for more troubleshooting tips.

== Organizing your init file ==

When your InitFile gets very long, it can be hard for you to organize it so that related customizations are near each other. See DotEmacsStructuring for tips.

